  "text": "In Section 2 we describe HiFST, which is a hierarchical phrase-based translation system based on the OpenFST WFST libraries [CITATION_1] . We describe how translation lattices can be generated over the Cocke-Younger-Kasami (CYK) grid used for parsing under Hiero. We also review some modeling issues needed for practical translation, such as the efficient handling of source language deletions and the extraction of statistics for minimum error rate training. This requires running HiFST in \"alignment mode\" (Section 2.3) to find all the rule derivations that generate a given set of translation hypotheses.",
